'''Effective Altruism Global''', abbreviated EA Global, is a series of [[philanthropy]] conferences that focuses on the [[effective altruism]] movement.<ref name="cea1">{{cite web|title=Centre for Effective Altruism Announces Lineup for Effective Altruism Global 2015|url=http://www.pitchengine.com/pitches/00ffe1e9-9189-4dc8-9e7a-5595fb90f61b|website=Pitchengine|publisher=Centre for Effective Altruism|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref> The conferences are run by the [[Centre for Effective Altruism]] at [[Oxford University]].<ref name="aboutpage">{{cite web|title=About EA Global|url=http://eaglobal.org/about|website=EA Global|publisher=Centre for Effective Altruism|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref> [[Huffington Post]] editor [[Nico Pitney]] described the events as a gathering of "nerd altruists", which was "heavy on people from technology, science, and analytical disciplines".<ref name="huffpo2">{{cite news|last1=Pitney|first1=Nico|title=Elon Musk To Address ‘Nerd Altruists’ At Google HQ|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/elon-musk-google-effective-altruism_us_55a56626e4b04740a3de3130|accessdate=4 April 2016|publisher=[[Huffington Post]]|date=July 16, 2015}}</ref>
==History== [[File:AI Existential Risk panel at EA Global.jpg|thumb|Panel with [[Nick Bostrom]], [[Elon Musk]], Nate Soares, and [[Stuart J. Russell|Stuart Russell]] during EA Global 2015]] An original Effective Altruism Summit was hosted in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.exponentialtimes.net/videos/jaan-tallinns-keynote-effective-altruism-summit-2013|title = Jaan Tallinn's Keynote - Effective Altruism Summit 2013 |date = November 13, 2013|accessdate = April 11, 2015|publisher = Exponential Times}}</ref>
In 2015, there were three main EA Global events. The largest was a three-day conference that took place on the [[Google]] campus in [[Mountain View, California]] with speakers including entrepreneur [[Elon Musk]], computer scientist [[Stuart J. Russell]], and Oxford philosophy professor [[William MacAskill]]. There were also conferences in [[Oxford]], [[United Kingdom|UK]] and [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]. According to MacAskill, the nature of the conferences improved coordination and ideological diversity within effective altruism. Talks included subjects such as "global poverty, animal advocacy, cause prioritization research, and policy change". There were also workshops on choosing careers, Q&A sessions, and panels on running local EA chapters.<ref name="huffpo1">{{cite news|last1=Guan|first1=Melody Y.|title=Elon Musk, Superintelligence, and Maximizing Social Good: A Weekend at History’s Largest Gathering of "Effective Altruists"|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/melody-y-guan/elon-musk-superintelligen_b_7929960.html|accessdate=4 April 2016|publisher=[[Huffington Post]]|date=August 3, 2015}}</ref>
At the Google conference, a moderated panel featured [[Elon Musk]] with AI researchers on the topic of [[existential risk from artificial general intelligence]].<ref name="inc">{{cite news|last1=Townsend|first1=Tess|title=Elon Musk: AI Is Going to Happen. Let's Prepare For It|url=http://www.inc.com/tess-townsend/musk-says-prepare-for-ai.html|accessdate=4 April 2016|publisher=[[Inc. Magazine]]|date=August 3, 2015}}</ref> Panel member [[Stuart J. Russell|Stuart Russell]] stated that AI research should be about "building intelligent systems that benefit the human race".<ref name="huffpo1" /> [[Vox (website)|Vox]] writer [[Dylan Matthews]] criticized the event for its perceived focus on [[existential risk]], potentially at the expense of more mainstream causes like fighting [[extreme poverty]].<ref name="matthews">{{cite news|last1=Matthews|first1=Dylan|title=I spent a weekend at Google talking with nerds about charity. I came away … worried.|url=https://www.vox.com/2015/8/10/9124145/effective-altruism-global-ai|accessdate=4 April 2016|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|date=August 10, 2015}}</ref>
EA Global 2016 was held on the UC Berkeley campus in August,<ref name="eag2016">{{cite web|title=EA Global 2016|url=http://eaglobal.org/|website=EA Global|publisher=Centre for Effective Altruism|accessdate=7 September 2016}}</ref>. EA Global 2017 was held at The Palace of Fine Arts Exhibition Center,<ref name="eag2017">{{cite web|title=EA Global 2017|url=https://www.eaglobal.org/events/ea-global-2017-san-francisco/|website=EA Global|publisher=Centre for Effective Altruism|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> and EA Global 2018 was held at Bespoke Events.<ref name="eag2018">{{cite web|title=EA Global 2018|url=https://www.eaglobal.org/events/ea-global-2018-san-francisco/|website=EA Global|publisher=Centre for Effective Altruism|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>
